definition.value: An optically active form of ornithine having L-configuration.
An oxime obtained via formal condensation of pyruvic acid with hydroxylamine.
A ribonucleic acid that is ribosomal RNA (rRNA) in which one of the RNA nucleotides is 2'-O-methyladenosine 5'-monophosphate.
A member of the class of phosphonic acids that is phosphonic acid in which the hydrogen attached to the phosphorous is replaced by a carboxymethyl group.
A galactobiose consisting of an alpha-D-galactofuranose residue and a beta-D-galactopyrannose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of a D-glucopyranose residue and a beta-D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A methylaniline that is  aniline carrying a methyl substituent at the nitrogen atom.
